01/02/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis assured UN Secretary General Kofi Annan in a telephone conversation on Saturday (31 January) that Greece would contribute to the efforts to resolve the Cyprus dispute in every possible way.
The telephone conversation was Simitis's initiative and is part of a broader effort to increase communication on the issue between him, Foreign Minister George Papandreou and Annan.
(MPA - 31/01/04)
